  </section>

  {%- comment -%}FAQ{%- endcomment -%}
  <section class="lp-faq" aria-label="Frequently asked questions">
    <div class="lp-faq__inner">
      <div class="lp-faq__head">
        <p class="lp-faq__eyebrow bbi-mono">Common questions</p>
        <h2>What clinics and facilities ask before sending the PO.</h2>
        <p class="lp-faq__cta">Still have a question? <a href="tel:18008359565">Call 1-800-835-9565</a> or <a href="/pages/quote">request a quote</a> and we&rsquo;ll respond in 1 business day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="lp-faq__list">

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">01</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Do you supply furniture for private clinics, not just hospitals?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; most of our healthcare clients are private practices: dental offices, physiotherapy clinics, walk-in clinics, medical offices, and family health teams. We also work with hospitals, long-term care facilities, and community health centres. The same commercial-grade product lines and free space-planning service apply regardless of organization size.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">02</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">What surfaces are cleanable / infection-control safe?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>We spec upholstery with antimicrobial treatment and sealed or impervious surfaces on request &mdash; common choices include vinyl, polyurethane, and antimicrobial woven fabrics. Hard surfaces (laminates, steel frames, solid polymer) clean easily with standard hospital-grade disinfectants. Tell us your cleaning protocol and we&rsquo;ll recommend finishes that are approved for it.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">03</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Can Ontario hospitals buy under OECM without a tender?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes. Brant Business Interiors is an OECM Supplier Partner (Agreement 2025-470). Hospitals, long-term care facilities, and other OECM-eligible Ontario organizations can purchase directly from us without an open tender or RFP. We&rsquo;ll provide the agreement number on the quote. If you&rsquo;re not sure whether your organization qualifies, call us &mdash; we&rsquo;ll confirm in five minutes.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">04</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">Does the quote include a space plan for the waiting room or reception area?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>Yes &mdash; every quote includes a free furniture layout. Send us your floor plan (even a rough sketch or PDF) and we&rsquo;ll place the pieces, spec the finishes, and show you the layout before you approve anything. This is especially useful for reception areas and waiting rooms where patient flow and sight lines matter.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="lp-faq-item">
          <summary>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__num">05</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__q">How does delivery and installation work at a clinical site?</span>
            <span class="lp-faq-item__icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          </summary>
          <div class="lp-faq-item__body">
            <p>We deliver across Ontario and coordinate around your patient schedule &mdash; early morning, after hours, or weekend delivery is available for occupied clinical buildings. Our installation crew handles uncrating, assembly, placement, and full debris removal so the space is patient-ready when they leave. For phased fit-outs or multi-floor facilities, we plan delivery windows with your operations team.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

